The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Govt clearance sought on Intikhab

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 PCA Coach

 Calcutta: The Punjab Cricket 

 Association (PCA) has decided to again employ former Pakistan 

 captain and coach Intikhab Alam as its coaching supremo. 

 This decision was taken at the 

 PCAs working committee meeting on Saturday. 

 Were formally writing 

 to the Indian government (through the sports ministry) for 

 permission to again get Inty on board. He will be formally 

 approached once the clearance comes from New Delhi. That 

 shouldnt take long, PCA president Inderjit Singh 

 Bindra told The Telegraph.

 Intikhab, it may be recalled, 

 coached Punjab in the last two seasons.




